Kubernetes Cluster Creation Using kOps on AWS
Complete Step-by-Step Handbook
Objective
This guide explains how to create a production-style Kubernetes cluster on AWS using kOps. By the end of this exercise, you will:
	Create a Kubernetes cluster using kOps
	Provision 1 Control Plane and 2 Worker Nodes
	Validate cluster health
	Deploy workloads
	Schedule Pods to a specific node
	Understand Node Affinity and Anti-Affinity concepts
	Safely destroy the cluster to avoid AWS charges

1. What is kOps?
kOps (Kubernetes Operations) is an open-source tool used to deploy, manage, upgrade, and maintain production-grade Kubernetes clusters on AWS.
kOps automates the creation of:
	VPC
	Subnets
	Security Groups
	EC2 Instances
	Auto Scaling Groups
	IAM Roles
	Route Tables
	Kubernetes Control Plane
	Worker Nodes
Think of kOps as Terraform specifically designed for Kubernetes.

