9. Schedule Pod to a Specific Node
Step 1: View Nodes
kubectl get nodes
Example:
worker1
worker2

Step 2: Label Target Node
kubectl label node worker1 dedicated=frontend
Verify:
kubectl get nodes --show-labels

Step 3: Deploy Pod Using Node Selector
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod

metadata:
  name: nginx-specific

spec:

  nodeSelector:
    dedicated: frontend

  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx
Apply:
kubectl apply -f nginx-specific.yaml
Verify:
kubectl get pod nginx-specific -o wide
Expected:
NODE
worker1

10. Node Affinity
Production Preferred Method.
Example:
affinity:
  nodeAffinity:
    requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
      nodeSelectorTerms:
      - matchExpressions:
        - key: dedicated
          operator: In
          values:
          - frontend
Benefits:
	Flexible
	Scalable
	Production Ready

11. Pod Anti-Affinity
Goal:
Do not place application replicas on the same node.
Example:
affinity:
  podAntiAffinity:
    requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
    - labelSelector:
        matchExpressions:
        - key: app
          operator: In
          values:
          - nginx
      topologyKey: kubernetes.io/hostname
Result:
Replica 1 -> Worker 1
Replica 2 -> Worker 2
Improves:
	High Availability
	Fault Tolerance
	Disaster Recovery

