13. Cluster Cleanup
IMPORTANT
Always delete the cluster after practice.
Delete:
kops delete cluster \
--name ${CLUSTER_NAME} \
--state ${KOPS_STATE_STORE} \
--yes
Verify EC2 Instances Removed:
aws ec2 describe-instances
Delete S3 Bucket:
aws s3 rb s3://test-kops-state-2026 --force

Interview Questions
What is kOps?
kOps is an open-source Kubernetes lifecycle management tool that automates the creation, upgrade, and maintenance of Kubernetes clusters on AWS.
Why is an S3 bucket required?
The S3 bucket acts as the kOps State Store where cluster configurations and metadata are stored.
Difference Between Node Selector and Node Affinity?
Node Selector:
	Simple
	Exact match
Node Affinity:
	Advanced scheduling
	Supports expressions and preferences
What is Pod Anti-Affinity?
Pod Anti-Affinity prevents multiple replicas from running on the same node, improving application availability during node failures.
Why use kOps instead of kubeadm?
kOps automatically provisions AWS infrastructure and manages the entire cluster lifecycle, while kubeadm only bootstraps Kubernetes on existing servers.
